    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Intake, Inlet, and Exhaust Manifolds -
        Cleaning and Inspection - Intake Manifold
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="0">
        <title>Intake Manifold</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, do not attempt to grind or machine the intake manifold to compensate for a
                    warped condition.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean inlet manifold thoroughly with a suitable non-caustic solvent.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After cleaning, blow dry using filtered
                <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check manifold for cracks and damage. Replace intake manifold as necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
